caption: First time visiting this restaurant and was blown away by the service and food. I have not been to Little Italy for some time and was sad to hear Ciao Bella was closed and wanted to go to an authentic Italian restaurant for my husbands birthday. We were a party of 5 and placing the reservation was easy. The atmosphere is welcoming with beautiful artwork. The menu is small but that shows the food is made fresh and I enjoyed having a small selection. Food was delicious and large serving amount for both appetizers and entrees. The part that made our visit over the top was our waiter Anthony. We had questions to get recommendations and he was knowledgeable and passionate about the menu. He checked on us in a consistent way that was not overwhelming or invasive and we were happy to see him each time. I know this review cannot guarantee a raise but Anthony deserves an award or recognition for his amazing service. If anyone is looking for authentic Italian cuisine in a lovely and relaxing environment, this is the place for you.
Spacious and socially distanced..very friendly staff..great foos..enjoyed the visit.

Every time I dine here, I get a different, wonderful experience. The staff provide an excellent, positive customer experience. The food is amazing; I suggest the exquisite Linguine Telleggio with shrimp. The decor is welcoming and comfortable. Also, try Javier's Amaretto Sour, you've never had better!!  I adore this place and you should too! Please support this restaurant, it is worth your time and money!♥️♥️♥️
One of the finest Italian restaurants that I have ever eaten at. Authentic Italian Food. Excellent choice. I highly recommend

Our dining experience at La Tavola was absolutely amazing! We had the burrata and a special for an appetizer. It was so full of flavor! Even the bread they give you before the meal (which is house made) was delicious! My husband had the rockfish cooked in the parchment paper and I has the spaghetti al Granchio (voted best dish in Baltimore for a reason). The bartender Anthony made any drink imaginable.  And please get a dessert. You will not regret it.
This restaurant provides superb service as well as delightful menu. My favourite spot ever. The meals came out rapidly and the rates were fair. I recommend this place.
The food was great as always!! I continue to go back!!
Good site for delicious Italian food. Food with real quality ingredients.  Mood here is similar to Fresno's scene.
Our favorite restaurant. The food is creative and delicious, the waiter staff is attentive. A wonderful dining experience. A must accommodate restaurant!

I want to give a big thank you to Anthony, his staff & the Chef.  My daughter’s 21st Birthday celebration with family was awesome. Loved that we had a separate upstairs area to ourselves. During these times people want to be and feel safe. You guys went above and beyond that. Contact tracing, temperature checks, sanitizing and more than 6 feet spacing.   Very accommodating to my needs and guests. Awe the food......hats off to the 👩‍🍳.
Always a  superb, stunning and exquisite dining experience!  Kudos to Chef Carlo and staff!!

Expensive, small portions, and just not that great. Really unimpressed with this place.  We ordered the fritto misto, lasagna bolognese, and linguini con taleggio e tartufo. The fritto misto had approximately 8 rubbery calamari, 2 boiled shrimp, and fried vegetables. Just very sad looking for the amount of money it was. The lasagna bolognese and linguini were ok, but not great, and again the portions were entirely too small for the cost.  Skip this place, there’s a lot better pasta in little Italy elsewhere.
Great food!  Very allergy friendly.  Great gluten free pasta!  Excellent service!
We had a fantastic time at La Tavola. Chris was very attentive, funny and his recommendations were spot-on. We will definitely be visiting this restaurant the next time we are in Baltimore.
Great food, great service.
Javi was a wonderful server! Food was delectable
Javier was the best server! He made the experience so much better. Food and service were amazing.
italian food and the atmosphere here is super good. You won't be disappointed in the menu and service. Really nothing but enjoyable experiences here, I'll be back.
Wonderful environment, terrific service, and delicous food. Would HIGHLY recommend. All seafood served is caught by the chef himself!

Unfortunately got there an hour before closing. This must have affected the quality of food which was served cold. My chicken Saltimbocca which I've had just about every place that serves it & this was the worst. Chicken was tough and slimy. Not good at all.
I like this restaurant very much. theres a happy ambiance. The meals are superb. the service is effective and the stuff is very professional. The price is reasonable. deeply recommend.

Great restaurant. We came Saturday afternoon. Everything was perfect. Food is top notch. Our server Javier went above and beyond to make our meal a wonderful experience. Indoor and well spaced . Outdoor dining is also an option. Plenty of parking. I can't wait to come back. Highly recommended
Delicious food! Impeccable service! Havi took great care of our table and went above and beyond. Best restaurant in Little Italy by far!!
Excellent food and excellent service. Javier and Anthony were amazing. They made our experience unforgettable. Best restaurant in Little Italy by far and we’ve been everywhere!

Javier was our server and Anthony was our host... both were phonemal to our party of 6. We went during the COVID-19 scare and decided to sit outside - they were very accommodating to us. Excellent service, excellent food.

Chris our server was amazing! The food was fantastic. We had the Polla Alla Florentine and Pesce Cartoccio and could not have asked for a better meal to celebrate our anniversary. We started off with the bruschetta and their bread they make in house is enough to make your mouth water.

The food was incredible.  Nothing beats house made freash pasta.  My fiancee lasagna and my ravioli were to die for.  It was nice to have fantastic food during a awful pandemic.  I look forward to returning on my next trip to Baltimore.
My top spot for delicious Italian food. The staff was sociable and attentive.
love the place, the atmosphere and the food.  Would be there more often if prices were more affordable.

A fav spot for italian food. Service is always awesome even when they have a full house. Definitely worth a return trip. This place has a good atmosphere. Reminds me of a cafe in Chicago I loved to visit.
Great experience. Terrific and personable service. I had the best lasagna of my life. Sorry I can only give 5 stars. La Tavola is a definite must go to.
Went downtown on out boat. Stopped off because of great reviews. Did not let us down. Great service. Great flavors. Chris was on point with suggestions and service. Will be back.
Not your everyday Italian restaurant. Menu is small but well designed. Food fresh and dishes were prepared prefectly. Will definitely return!
The food was amazing, our waiter was kind and knowledgeable about the food, and the drinks were very good. Fantastic experience, and we plan to come again soon

I’ve been to other restaurants in Little Italy before but this is definitely my favorite. We went for the first time last night and had the best experience!! The staff was great and funny, and the food was so delicious. I will 100% be coming back here

The best Italian experience in Baltimore! Just returned from out of state and decided to have dinner. Not the first time eating here but everytime has been a wonderful experience. The food is excellent!!! Chris our server was so attentive and made the experience even more enjoyable. Highly recommend.
Had a wonderful experience tonite. Food and service top notch. The bolognese sauce is really special. Highly recommended.
Outstanding location for tasty italian food. Visited on Sat I believe. The bill was good for how much you get.

What an incredible experience. My boyfriend and I went to la tolva after a long car ride and could not of picked a better place. It’s a hidden gem. The food left us speechless. Our waiter Anthony was so accommodating and a truly phenomenal guy. He made us feel special by going above and beyond to make sure we enjoyed our experience there. We definitely will be going back everytime we go to Baltimore. Such a genuine place with great people, food, and ambiance. 10/10 would recommend! Thank you for making our trip so memorable.

I don't usually leave reviews, but the dinner my boyfriend and I had tonight was one of the best we've ever had, the service alone deserves five stars. We will definitely be back, and will be bringing friends.

The food is authentic. Drinks were great. Service was excellent! Javier and chris were awesome.Excellent meal and service! Our server Chris did an outstanding job, not intrusive but always there at the right time. He poured a superb glass of wine - no drip AND no napkin needed for his pours! Carlo’s taste and texture combinations are always spectacular. The sea bass with scallops was perfectly done and seasoned. Highly recommend!
I’d stop by as often as I can to grub here. The service is cheerful and fast. Everyone dining here is in a good mood because they know about and are eating great food.

This is the best Italian food I've had outside of Italy.  Chef Carlo's attention to detail, ability to blend flavors with fresh ingredients, and passion for quality makes this place fabulous.  The staff is wonderful as well.  We had a 4 day visit and ate there 3 times!! I highly recommend doing the chef's choice.  Worth every penny.  You will not be disappointed

The food was very good (not as good as my first visit last year) and very different from your typical Italian restaurant. Everything is freshly made for each patron, never pre-prepared and warmed up; they make all of their own pasta and breads. Desserts are scrumptious, especially the large scoop of coffee/vanilla gelato covered in chocolate/Expresso syrup and slivers of coconut. Our waiter Anthony was solicitous and full of personality.
Affordable Wine and Entrees, great atmosphere and delicious food.
Delectable
Relaxed atmosphere,  knowledgeable wait staff, wonderful food.

La Tavola cured my Italian craving amazingly. Everything is made fresh, in house, by the chef. From the bread, to the pastas, Caesar dressing, raviolis, etc. The Caesar salad was delicious with their homemade dressing. The raviolis were phenomenal, albeit I had them made with Vodka sauce instead of cream sauce. Absolutely fantastic dinner. The wait staff all seemed knowledgeable, with my waiter Alex being friendly and on top of my excessive amount of water refills. Highly recommend.
Dessert was great, dessert martini was as well. Not super impressed with the food. It was during restaurant week so I would give it another shot and update this post when I do
Good food. Reasonably priced. Knowledgeable staff.
Food
Mouthwatering pasta... can't wait to go there again

Chef Carlo is so good with food. We had a shrimp and anchovies appetizer. A dish from Venice,Italy. This was delicious words can't detail this appetizer.  The kitchen did a fantastic job with my entree, puttanesca.  If I could have, I would have sopped up the sauce (tomatoe gravy) with bread. I was to full. However, was able to have a shared dessert called cheese cake a la Carlo. This with a cup of coffee was soooooo good. If you can try this great Italian restaurant in little Italy,Baltimore, do so!
Delicious food, knowledgeable staff, chef came out to check on my allergies to prepare exactly what I could eat.
Terrible. Chain restaurant vibe and food. Over priced for no reason.
This restaurant is fantastic from the quality of the food to the service to the ambiance. I'll definitely be back!
Extremely good.
Extremely fabulous food, cordial staff, great pricing, fresh options, and great mood. You should definitely try this place!

Enjoyed this dining experience so much. Service was superior.... As was the food. My son and daughter-in-law treated me for resturant week and I felt like a queen! Oh, get the Lemon drop cocktail..made in house.

Restaurant week here has lots of sea food, and classic Italian entrees.  The well lit dining room was inviting for conversations. Severs and wait staff knew the menu well and gave advice that was helpful.  I had OSSOBUCCO. It was tender  but slightly bland. My husband had lasagna, he loved it.  It was a good evening but won't become a regular "go to spot". However it a great first date spot.
Very good food
Excellent food and service
Food was incredible. Service was awesome.  We will be back!
The food was perfectly prepared and in large portions.
the service was great the atmosphere and plates were beautiful but the taste was just not therr
Everything was just fantastic.
Nice place for a dinner party. Good food. The spinach ravioli was very tasty.
My dad and my favorite place to get pasta.  Tge tiramisu is not to be missed
Cozy ambiance and great service
Absolutely divine food. The fresh made pasta is wonderful!!
Great atmosphere excellent service ..food is delicious
Good food
Elegance at a very reasonable price
Great food and Javier provided great service.
Great food and atmosphere but pricey
Wonderful!

My experience unlike others was very bad I got some uncooked gnocchi in my spaghetti dish and I almost gagged my dish had very minimal pasta and was $28 the actual seafood was very gritty, all in all not a great experience but I hope you enjoy your experience.
Amazing service, the food was fresh and yummy, and the staff were incredible. Special shoutout to Anthony and Keith (our waiter)! Will definitely be back soon!

The food here is not only incredibly tasty, but arranged into beautiful presentations.  I recommend couples get two appetizers, and then share a first course and an entree. It was the perfect amount of food for us.

Prefix dinner for 30 in the upstairs room. Appetizers of shrimp and calamari was decent, the eggplant app was great.  Dinner of spaghetti and chicken marsala was fine. Would have loved to have been able to order off the menu.
Food was just ok. The calamari was excellent!
Polished and very clam place for lunch and dinner
Tastes just like food I've had in Italy before. Delicious.
Good food! Nice sit-down! Nice staff!
Perfect meal after surgery. Yummy house made pasta in creamy sauce with mushrooms. Mmmhm comfort food!
Really good food.  Wonderful staff
Charged for 2 kids meals when I clearly stated they would share. Pasta was under cooked. Prices are a little high for what you get.
Fantastic food and service.
The Carbonara with extra chicken sub fettuccine pasta... sooo goood
Local people love it.
Absolutely delicious. Wonderful meal. Everything was incredibly tasty and satisfying
Try the black squid ink spaghetti, made in house. An interesting variation on a popular Venitian dish.
High-quality food, a pay-parking lot around the corner, not busy during lunch time on a weekend, a bit pricey but worth the splurge when looking for well-balanced/flavored Italian food
Good atmosphere & nice food
The BEST Italian restaurant in Baltimore
Great food. Great service. Great ambiance. I'll be back!
Good food, but expensive comparatively speaking.
Good food and service, but smaller portion sizes than we expected for the price.
Great food and amazing service. Highly recommend. Half price bottles of wine on Wednesday was a bonus.  Don’t forget to get a dessert.
Great food and great service.

I have NEVER awarded 5 *'s to a place in Baltimore's Little Italy dining district. Why? Simply put, I had somehow missed this glorious Chef and his Kitchen staff. PASTA, mad in house and delicious. We tried the three tiered meal, app, entree and desert for around $35. with a glass of their San Giovese. The lasagna bolognese was extraordinary. Best ever. Some Clown said here that the place could use an update, whatever. I don't want to pay 25% more for new this and that as long as food and service are at the current level. Chris, our seasoned Waiter was spot on. I'll be back again and again.
Very nice place
amazing calamari appetizer and pasta dishes

It was okay. When we arrived the kitchen staff was "on break" so we waited a short time before ordering. We wanted to do the Chef's Tasting, but he was off so the waitress recommended against it. Our entrees were okay, but pretty bland. Overall it was okay food but overpriced for the final product. Maybe we had an off night but I won't be trying again.
(Translated by Google) Tasty average. Not cheap  (Original) טעים ממוצע. לא זול

Food is amazing, service is excellent. Do yourself a favor and check this place out. I hadn't been to Baltimore in about 8 years and just came back. La Tavola was as good as I remembered! It is hard to meet expectations of a long lost good memory but this was as good as I remembered!
Wonderful

After searching Google for the best nearby pasta restaurants I was directed to La Tavola.  I was visiting from out of town and it was convenient to my hotel and the parking was easy. Service was prompt, efficient and pleasant. I was seated without a reservation easily. To my delight it was restaurant week in Baltimore and I had a 3 course dinner for a reasonable fixed price.   Their lasagna was delicious with in house homemade pasta. The cheesecake portion seemed small until I realized how rich it was. I felt pleasantly full afterwards.  I would like to go back to try some of the other entrees later.
Simply the best Italian food and dining experience in Baltimore.  Special thanks to Chef Carlo!!
Best Italian restaurant I have ever been to - Dave was the man!!!!
Man oh man what a meal.  Staff is awesome, food is amazing, and the deal for resturant week was unbeatable
The food was great and the service was wonderful.

First time at this restaurant!  We were lucky to be there for restaurant week and had a wonderful 3 course dinner for $35.  Food was delicious.   We will definitely go back next time we are in Baltimore.
Great food and the service was good.  I would eat here again.
So so
Homemade pasta, cooked perfectly al dente. The chef came around and spoke with us. The server gave me good recommendations about local activities. Great ambiance, great food, great service.

Fresh fish from the Bay.  Fantastic grilled vegetables. The restaurant serves great food and has an amazing, friendly staff who were sensitive to food allergies.  Also a pleasure to meet Chef Carlo.  Grazie Mille!

My husband took me here for my birthday because I love Italian food  As we were walking up, we saw a cook outside harvesting basil for use in the kitchen.  The food is incredibly good. The pasta is fantastic and clearly hand made (and amazing). The salads and appetizers were wonderful (I usually hate calamari and got talked into trying some and I actually liked it). The desserts we ordered were perfect.  And the staff are amazingly friendly and attentive. 100% the hour drive from the DC metro area. We will be going there again and again. It's possibly my new favorite place

I went there as part of a large group of persons and we sat in the upper floor. The restaurant was relatively small, the food very tasty and well prepared but the quantities were not adapted to the size of the groups.

THe aesthetic look of the place is very subtle, yet elegant. The food blew us away. The quality of the food is higher than any other Italian restaurant in the Baltimore area. The people & The service are very caring, and kind. The simplicity of this restaurant is what makes it the best. We really enjoyed dining in this restaurant!
Everything was perfect! Very knowledgeable staff, especially our server, Chris, and the chef right now is from Venice!
Really enjoyed our meal here.  Waitress was very friendly.  Ambiance upstairs was lacking.
Great for special occasions. Recommend making reservations

Outstanding service from all waitstaff. Chef was amazing. Food is farm to table vegetables and all else house made including regular & gluten free pasta. Could not have asked for a better dining experience!

Oh my gosh. This entire experience was incredible. All of the wait staff (especially Maki and Anthony) were just amazing. So attentive and skilled. The food was perfectly prepared and in large portions. It was just a wonderful experience from start to finish.
Good service and food

Great Italian place. They make everything in house and fresh. Our server, Jeannie was super friendly and knowledgeable. My wife had the gnocchi al pesto, which was slightly under-seasoned but perfectly cooked, and perfect texture. I had the spinach and ricotta ravioli, which was amazing. The tiramisu did not disappoint either. Sorry for the bad pictures.. They keep it dim and cozy inside.
Lovely atmosphere, great service, and incredible, fresh food!!
(Translated by Google) Bellisimo, bellisimo, bellisimo. Very well.  (Original) Bellisimo, bellisimo, bellisimo. Molto bene.

Serving dependable Italian food in a cozy location, La Tavola makes for a great night out in Little Italy. We started with the eggplant appetizer, followed with the ravioli special and then finished off with the house cannoli. The eggplant was a definite highlight of the meal. Everything was well prepared and the wait staff were very knowledgeable of the menu. Prices are reasonable, and they have house bottles of wine. Like many other Little Italy restaurants, the place could use a bit of an update but it also adds to the charm of eating in this area.
Excellent service, quiet, warm atmosphere. Delicious food.
Excellent fresh made pasta. Creative house designed cocktails. Good service. Relaxed yet slightly upscale ambiance. Reasonable prices for the fresh, fresh, fresh ingredients!
Nice antipasto, comforting ravioli and seafood pasta and good service by our hostess, Jeannie!

What an beautiful dinner and evening tonight. We were gifted the Chef’ Choice dinner and Chef Carlo designed a delicious 4 course experience and even paired a perfect wine for us. Starting with an appetizer with calamari, pasta round with lobster linguine and lasagna, main course of scallops and sea bass and then a sampler dessert of chocolate chip cheesecake and tiramisu. Our waitress, Maki, was friendly and knowledgeable. She made it such a lovely evening. Thank you so much.
Very courteous and helpful staff, and the homemade pasta was delicious.
Really solid Italian food. The sauces are fantastic - we had the gnocchi with cream and pesto sauce and the lasagne. Both are really good! Jeannie our waitress and Carlo the chef are great!
Expensive, but the food was ok.
Very good italian!

Delicious food. Even though they seem to specialize in sea food, I ordered a chicken dish and thought it was absolutely fantastic, and the bits of pasta I stole from my dining partners were really special in texture and taste. The bar area looks really swanky, but the main dining area a bit less so, so it's more about the food at this restaurant than atmosphere. One minor weak point, I thought, was the bread they served before the orders came out. They included two types. One type was great, but the other seemed surprisingly generic. But, it was easy to get over that quibble once the main courses arrived!
The food is very good.  Great customer service. Its a beautiful restaurant.
Delicious
Service was excellent, dishes were made in house and filling I will definitely return.
Went here on a whim based off the reviews and can say this is one of the BEST Italian joints I’ve been to. Food was amazing! Service and staff were friendly and attentive. Will definitely be back!

I'm in the restaurant business for 30 years. After a long day of traveling and setting in we were met with attitude and looks. These people think they can treat people poorly. Umm. Helloooo. Too many restaurants in walking distance to choose from. I'd choose 0 stars if it we're an option. Terrible ownership and management.

Best place for Italian food in Baltimore. Located in the heart of Little Italy, la Tavola makes handmade pasta and creative dishes daily. We love visiting when we are in the area. They are very community oriented and are always striving to serve their local patrons!

I really wanted to love this place but I only liked it. The opening spiel delivered by the waitress about farm to table and the owner being from Venice set my expectations kind of high. However, having been to Venice (and other cities in Italy), the sliced Turkey in the meat and olive tray (with a sliver of cheese) didn't feel very Venetian. Also, my boyfriend got a seafood bowl (can't remember exact name) and the shrimp was definitely overcooked, although, he did enjoy the rest of the seafood. As for the veal lasagna I got, I liked it but didn't love it.
An Italian restaurant with American portions and great wine.
Delicious food, excellent service. The staff was knowledgeable and helpful with suggestions. Great value for quality food, highly recommended.
Waiter very helpful and accommodate my eating habits I'm diabetic and everything he work with to help me out very well thank you

Food was excellent and the service was phenomenal. The staff are friendly and work well together and the entire place was clean and neat. I recommend take it a hard look here if you're looking for top tier pasta!

I've been here a few times now, Its by far my absolute favorite Italian Restaurant. I highly recommend The Chef's Special and Meeting Carlos and all that he has to offer!  Multiple photos of multiple meals had!

Five stars. Ask for Allison. This is a top class Italian restaurant in little Italy. Everything homemade. The chef is from Venice. The food is to die for. Homemade pasta fresh everyday. Great service. Wonderful wine list. Don't miss it
Great food. My favorite is the lasagna.  The pasta is made fresh.

Wow - just amazing Italian food. Homemade pastas and unique dishes. Very comfortable space and very helpful and attentive service. Everything we had from appetizers to main dish to desserts to drinks were just top notch. Highly recommended
Excellent food and service. Large plates. The macaroni was cooked to perfection. We were a group of four and everyone was delighted with this restaurant
Amazon food and Eine, great service. A must egen in Baltimore!
Very nice place and friendly staff. Service is outstanding among Baltimore fine dining restaurants. Good food too overall very enjoyable dining experience.
Food is a bit pricey but is always good. Sometimes, they have groupons available during thier slow season. Please check for groupons first.. Love this place. The service is always good!

The wife and I went on our sixth anniversary. This was where we had our first date. We remembered the food to be good the first time, but this time it was exceptional.  We ordered the "Chefs choice". Chef Carlo came to the table and talked to is about what he direction he was going for our meal. He told us he was steering towards seafood based dishes as it was his specialty . I didn't consider myself a seafood guy. I like shrimp and crab but typically stay away from fish and never eat squid or scallops. Chef Carlo has changed my mind. I would now consider myself a GOOD seafood guy. Every course of our meal with exception of dessert was seafood based and absolutely delicious. I would order every one again. The Fritto Misto was a great start. The squid ink pasta was something that i would have never ordered prior but will now have a craving for. The Flounder was perfectly cooked. I honestly couldn't find ANYTHING that could have been done better. I give five stars because it won't let me give more.  Oh yeah and they have drinks with cool names like "The Dude Abides" which was a blueberry white Russian.

Attended a birthday party here in the small ballroom upstairs. Really great service and friendly staff. The appetizers and entrees were very very delicious. The dining area also had great ambiance. Would to go for a fine dinner soon.
I try to eat here every time I visit Baltimore, which is a few times a year. The food is always superb. The bread, olive oil, pasta, seafood, etc. are always very memorable.
Awesome everyone was smiling and very attentive 3 hours free parking Yeah! Get there abt 5:30pm
Definitely one my most favorite Italian restaurants! Fresh Ingredients, good bread!
Its okay .maybe I ordered the wrong dish. Ambience is great !!!

Stopped here on a whim for lunch while in town for the long weekend. Was hoping for decent Italian fare, got literally the best lasagna I've ever had -- and I love lasagna and order it frequently. Loved it so much I had to go out of my way to tell my waiter and the manager, who explained that the key is perfecting the bolognese sauce and bechamel, focusing on those over what he described as the too-common strategy of heaping on mounds and mounds of cheese. I'll never visit Baltimore again without coming back here and getting the lasagna. Service, pricing, location, ambience also all stellar.

We fell in love right away when Charlie gave us his favorites and the specials menu. He had us at hello lol.  My husband and I both tried a few of his faves and from the appetizers to desert we weren’t disappointed.  I suggest that if you’re in downtown Baltimore stop in to have Charlie from Portland, Oregon give you his personal take on leaving completely satisfied.  I only dabbled at each dish just so I, the foodie could take it home to have my delights again.
A truly fine place; excellent dinner with friendly staff.
Delicious food. We had the osso bucco with risotto and the grouper with vegetables  in parchment paper. Everything was cooked perfectly. The service was great too. We'll return.
Excellent food!
Perfect date spot!! Love the black spaghetti
Great food + drinks, service & accommodations for our Valentine’s Day dinner.

Fantastic meal as always, been here a few times and it never disappoints.  Staff are well informed about the food and wine and can answer any questions as well as being tentative and providing great service.
Excellent service and food.
Delicious. Great wait staff.
Great food and great service. The macchiato great.
Homemade pasta, good sauces, great service.
Love it. Both food and service was good
Truley excellent top service. Good food and reasonable prices
A great surprise in Little Italy of Baltimore. Venetian style Italian with good service and great pricing!
Quality food with old school service

Invited with some friends passing through town. Crab cakes ✔, fresh shrimps & cocktail sauce ✔, fresh seafood salad"horrible"😵 messed my stomach all up. Decor lol... Could be upgraded on a major level. Location is awesome plus there is parking around the corner from the restaurant. Owner was sweet and courteous

Some of the freshest ingredients. The pasta is all made fresh in house, as well as all of the desserts. We ordered a variety of pasta dishes with different sauces. The lasagna was, in my opinion, the BEST dish on the table.  I had a seafood pasta dish with white wine sauce which was very good but my shrimp were a little overcooked. We ordered the family plate of dessert and was not disappointed at all.
Customer service is superb! Prices are fair, food is good.
Service was outstanding and food was amazing
You must dine here to experience how good the food is. Waiters are very courteous as well. What are you waiting for? GO!
If you're wondering if you should eat here, you should. 👍🏼
A great place for a holiday get-together :) They serve gluten free pasta options.
Great staff and good food. Enjoyed our Christmas Day lunch.
Awesome restaurant. Went here for dinner. Food was amazing. Servers were very friendly. Great dining experience. Highly recommend and will definitely return.
Phenomenal meal and phenomenal service! I'd recommend this place to any and everybody! We're already planning our next trip.
Nice food though somewhat pricey. Sandwich, appetizer, soup 3 nothing special drinks 72.00.

A wonderful Italian restaurant in Baltimore’s Little Italy, La Tavola  wouldn’t be out of place in Rome, Venice, or New York City. Service is fun, knowledgeable, and decidedly approachable. None of the stuffy airs you might expect with food of this quality. Chef is a Venetian who has graced Baltimore with his talents and love of good food. Go. Enjoy.

Chef Carlo is a creative genius in the kitchen. His hand made gnocchi melts in your mouth. The tortelloni in the Gorgonzola cheese sauce was amazing. The desserts were outstanding especially the homemade cream puffs. The holiday decorations are beautiful especially the fresh Christmas tree in the dining room. The staff was attentive and friendly.

Wonderful place to eat, everything we had was amazing. The lasagna is out of this world! The staff was on point the entire night, the chef came out and talked to every table as well. Truly worth the drive from Harford county!
Really good food and wine selection. Everything is made from scratch and you can tell the difference.

Had such a lovely Saturday night in Little Italy. Daniel, our waiter, was enthusiastic and knowledgeable, starting off by explaining the background of the restaurant and chef since it was our first time there.  I had been eyeing the Italian Lemonade cocktail on the menu before arriving and it was light and tasty. I was impressed with the fact that food is locally sourced and all pasta made on site. You could taste that quality in the vegetable penne I ordered. As a cannoli lover, I recommend their dessert offering as they  have reimagined it. Go and taste for yourself!
One of the best Italian I've had in a long time. Great vegetarian options. Don't miss out on the ravioli!
This is a wonderful place for friends meetup!
Excellent Italian food and God drink options
Wait staff was naturally friendly and extremely helpful in making food choices.  Adorable, enthusiastic  chef came from kitchen to make sure we were satisfied.  We were satisfied!
Wonderful meal. Proud waiters, fantastic flavors. Great combination.
Wonderful excellent love it
Delicious meal and Kim was a wonderful server.
Great food! Great service! Love the owner/chef that caught the fish he served himself the night prior. Prices are reasonable.

We went here for lunch. Start to finish this place is fantastic. Inexpensive lunch and dinner option. Good size portions, wonderful service and atmosphere. Everything they serve the make in house. The bread is to die for. We got a side of house made pasta with a bacon, crimini mushrooms, etc. I recommend getting the side or half orders. They are quite rich. I ordered the fish of the day which was rock fish and shrimp which were caught that morning. It’s steamed in a parchment bag with a white wine sauce with bruschetta tomatoes and artichokes. If I could give it more stars I would.

Had an awesome dining experience at La Tavola the night before the Baltimore marathon. Charlie, our waiter, was funny, knowledgeable, and passionate about the establishment. The bread and pasta is homemade, the seafood is fresh (and some caught by the head chef, himself!) and the owner, Carlo, was walking around all night chatting with customers and cracking jokes. The tiramisu was a delicious dessert, and the lasagna was excellent. Would recommend!
Best Italian food! Great service

Our meal was absolutely delicious and the scallops in it were to die for. The service was great as well. The only reason this isn't five stars is the cheesecake dessert was small and disappointing in flavor/ texture and there was a weird policy that you couldn't tip from gift certificates.

If I could give it more than 5 stars,  I would!!! Food was phenomenal, and the service was even better!! Highly recommend the Chef's special!!!! You will feel like royalty!!! Now I never want to try another restaurant in Baltimore,  because the bar was set way to high!!

Delicious! We came to town for a conference and thought for sure we should find some crabcakes. However, we ended up here out of luck. It was a Tuesday, and we did the three course meal with wine pairings for each course. Only $50 a person! It was great! I recommend the squid ink spaghetti with crab. So good.

One of the top-notch Italian restaurants we have visited. It wasn’t just about an impeccable service, or high quality/locally sourced cuisine, or creative and delightful pastries, but it’s the entire package & overall dining experience that makes La Tavola stand out amongst peers.  Food: Simply outstanding. For this visit, we ordered Antipasto Italiano as a classic starter, followed up with three different types of entree (Spaghetti Neri al Granchio from the menu and two specials – lamb & seafood), then sampled two kinds of dessert (one from the menu and one special) to conclude a perfect family dinner. We shared all the dishes so everyone could taste a little bit of everything and provided his/her own comments. So what’s the verdict? Essentially thumbs up from everyone and I would say that’s a pretty rare scenario!  Service: Excellent. Wait staffs were friendly, professional and very knowledgeable of the menu & specials. GM was very attentive, walking around the floor constantly to ensure guests on every table were well taking care of.  Atmosphere: Comfortable space, soft lighting with non-intrusive background music, cast iron and wood deco around the dining area and painting on the brick wall together create inviting warmth, casual and relax ambiance and project sense of tradition.  Take away: Given the wonderful dining experience and value it provided, we plan to visit La Tavola again next time when we visit Baltimore.

Food is amazing. Wait staff was incredibly friendly. One of my friends said the food was a little to spicy for his taste. And they never asked twice and remade his plate to perfection. Next time im in town. I will definitely come back. 5 stars all day :)
Awesome service and great homemade pasta!
The pasta was amazing. Staff was friendly and professional.
Eggplant parma and ink pasta were awesome. Very friendly.

The WORST EXPERIENCE EVER! The server Allison/Chris swiped my card twice without me knowing. When I brought it to their attention they did not want to reimburse me. They swiped my card for over $100! When asked to fix it they made me wait for almost an hour for a “letter” . I will never dine at this place again. The money is not an issue it is the principle, and they did not understand that. My advice to anyone paying with a card, make sure they charge the correct amount.

I went here for the first time with a large group for dinner. Traditionally, we go to another nearby restaurant with a similar name. We won't be doing that any more.  La Tavola was so inviting and accommodating when we called ahead. There was no hesitation to take the large group of over a dozen. When we got there, we were warmly greeted by our wait staff, and immediately felt at home. The food was rediculously delicious, and was only second to the service provided.  Don't hesitate to visit.

Very good food and menu. The chef makes creative twists so it is not a traditional heavy Italian fare. The linguine with truffles and mushrooms was exceptional as were the desserts.  Not a romantic setting but friendly and pleasant and not very loud even on a Friday night.  Our waitress was outstanding doing

Every bit as delicious as our last visit in May. I think it's my favorite restaurant in Bmore. Homemade pasta is to die for (not just the lasagna). Everything made to perfection.  I wish the bread would be warm when served and it took a bit too long for dinner to come out,  but 5 stars anyway because of how delicious everything is,  how fresh! Staff is FRIENDLY! Warm and welcoming. And GM Dave Olsen is a SWEETHEART! Dave... during my last visit in May, you had me try a drink concoction you were creating.  I suggested that you add champagne and serve it for Mother's Day. Did you? I asked you to name the Ellie. Too bad I didn't remember this at the restaurant earlier! Standing ovation!!!!
This is, without a doubt, the BEST restaurant in all of little Italy! The qualify of service, food ambience can't be beat here. Don't miss this place!
Food was great staff treated us wonderful special thanks to Kim.
Thanks again Carlo and staff! Always amazing food and service.
Outstanding service and the best food in little italy! Chef Carlo is awesome.

The food and service here is phenomenal! The menu is filled with so many tempting selections that it’s hard to choose, but that gives us a reason to go back right? Christian was the best server ever! He is personable, professional, and offers suggestions from the menu for the indecisive. The atmosphere was nice and the food arrived to the table promptly. I can’t remember the name of the dish, but the pasta with shiitake and pancetta was probably my favorite thing there.

Ate every bite of a delicious authentic Italian meal!  WoW! The staff and owner was very personable and polite coming to our table on a busy Saturday night making sure we were happy!  Will be back again soon!
I love the atmosphere and the food was so good i will definitely be coming back again
Great food, very good service, recommend to anyone

Venetian style Italian. It's not the usual cheesy pasta. Go elsewhere for that. But seafood Italian? You can't bypass this place. Go! Italian and Baltimore Crab? Perfect together. I've been to Venice. This chef is from that area. End of story. Great food.

This place will be my last here in Baltimore. I am very glad I have, our server Daniel. Was very knowledgeable and very eager to let is know about their food. Helpfull as well. When I mean us I mean we had a table of 8. We all had a great experience here. I do highly recommend this restaurant. Thank you La Tavola.
A  very interesting Italian restaurant in Baltimore. From farm to table, super fresh food. Good dinning environment.

This is a little hidden gem that is walking distance from the inner harbor area. The staff is friendly and the menu has many delicious options. The lasagne is absolutely fantastic! I highly recommend a visitvisit book you find yourself in the area.
Great food, freshly prepared. Hand made pasta. Casual. Large portions, moderately priced.
Fresh, high quality Italian food. Our server Charlie was a pleasure and very informative on the menu and food preparation
The service was absolutely amazing and the food was even better. Shout out to Charlie he is the nicest server I've ever met.

Service was amazing. Gnocchi was the beat I've ever had in my life. We started out with a pasta sample with crab meat, roasted tomatoes and ink infused pasta. Our server plated it for us and even asked the chef to give us more gnocchi because we were sharing between the two of us. Hands down the best Italian food I've ever had and will make the 2 hour drive to come back.

Went to a rehearsal dinner here last Friday evening and have nothing but good things to say.  The party was on the upper level in a private room and everything was wonderful.  The food was absolutely delicious!  The meal was served family style (not sure if that's how the entire restaurant is or not) and every dish was better than the last.  The ravioli were by far my favorite but we also had chicken piccata, chicken marsala, calamari and a rolled eggplant appetizer - all of which were equally delicious.  The dessert options were just as good as the meal and the wine selection was top notch.  Service was fantastic and everyone was so polite and helpful.  If we're ever in Baltimore again we will he stopping by.  The parking situation was less than ideal but I think that was more due to the baseball game down the street than anything.
Food & service were great.  Unique & standard dishes, fair prices, great service.
Great itallian food! The best restaurant in Baltimore. I recomed the Pesce and Occo.. (basically pork)
Great if you like your pasta al dente
I guess the food was okay, if you like food that has no flavor.
Great northern italian menu and very accommodating service.
The food was delicious and the service was top-notch.

Came here for a group dinner.  Very good service.  The eggplant rolatini was excellent, as was the chicken parmesan. I would love to return and have the seafood entrees. The chef seems to take much pride in his food!
Great place to eat nice staff signature desert is to die for. Well worth the trip.
Wonderful staff, delicious food, lovely neighborhood, highly recommended
Amazing  service! The tomato sauce is so fresh and delicious it’s sinful. Awesome bread too.
Everything is home made! You will not be disappointed.
Fantastic find in Little Italy,service is impeccable,food,is delicious and it has a great wine choice.The manager Dave couldn’t be more,helpful,highly recommended

Stopped here for lunch and enjoyed the food! I would love to visit during the chefs special. Definitely Venetian style food (seafood Italian) but has a lot of variety on the menu. The lasagna is worth writing home about
Excellent food, all fresh made, in- house. Service is great, very friendly and knowledgeable. Nice location and atmosphere. Loved it!

Great homemade pasta. We ordered one of the specials, which was rockfish caught by the chef himself. The burrata appetizer could have been warmer. The other 2 entrees off the menu  were delicious. Prices on the expensive side but everything is fresh and homemade. Would recommend for a nice night out in Little Italy.
Great little place with a personal touch, Awesome staff, excellent food, what more can you ask for.

Amazing food and wonderful employees.  Very welcoming and attentive.  Would definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting or living in the Baltimore downtown area.  Wished we lived closer to be able to go more.

We found this gem in Little Italy and were thrilled to get away from the touristy in we harbor.  The restaurant is cozy and quiet with tasteful and simple decor.  The service was outstanding from the moment we arrived.  Our waiter took the time to go over the specials for he day as well as several dishes on the menu.  He had a way with words that made you want to order it all.  The Carpaccio was delicious and so light.  We also tried the soup of the day which actually was lacking a bit in flavor.  Everything else tasted wonderful after that.  The Gnocchi was light and melted in our mouths.  The Spaghetti Neri was a great and the crab meat really completes the dish.  My favorite item was the Linguini alla Scoglio with scallops, muscles, clams, shrimp and a spicy red sauce.  The pasta is all homemade which makes for a better dish as well as the fresh seafood.  Whatever you do, save room for dessert.  The cheesecake was okay but the cannoli was the star with that fresh creamy filling.  To top off he night, it was 1/2 price bottles of wine...winning!
Fair. Neighborhood place

First time for my family to dine at La Tavola.  We were checking out the area's posted lunch menus and zeroed in on this one.  It was quiet when we came in, there were no other patrons.  (The weather was beautiful, the kind where one would expect people to be out and about OR to be at the beach!)  The interior gave out a warm (cozy) ambiance -- I personally loved the murals and earth-y color theme overall.  The server, Daniel, and "unnamed busboy" (I know, we should've asked for his name) were very cordial and accommodating.  The food (lunch) was great.  We ordered calamari and bruschetta for appetizers, and we weren't disappointed.  The calamari, especially, was thoughtfully served with veggie slices (nice touch!).  The entrées - pasta dishes - were all served hot and brimming with just the right flavors we were expecting.  The portions were just right.  We had to decline their in-house desserts because we always go to Vaccaro's for Italian sweets.  We were told by "unnamed busboy" that La Tavola's cannoli was the best he's ever had.  (We have no reason to doubt him so we might try it at another time.)  It has been a delightful midday meal experience for us at La Tavola.  Highly recommended!
Personal service, made to order

This place is really good but not excellent. Every dish was yummy but I wasn't impressed. It was very quiet in here when I came. But the service was attentive and the food was solid. For a more impressive Italian meal I'd visit La Scala.
The Lamb is delicious

First time visit 06/26/18.  My girlfriend and I thought it was excellent. The manager (owner?) and our waitress Maki were very personable and helpful.  Carolyn was able to order a very good low- lactose salad meal that wasn’t exactly on the …

We had a wonderful evening here after viewing The Incredibles nearby. The meal was great from the anti-pasto and cold beer through dessert; the atmosphere intimate for a good sized restaurant; and our waitperson, Maki, was a sheer delight!😘

The atmosphere in the restaurant gives off a romantic feeling. The music is led by Frank Sinatra and like artists. The food is the most authentic Italian food I have ever had the pleasure of tasting. This will be my first stop when I visit Baltimore next.
Great food. One of the best places in little Italy. Get the eggplant parm
Chef Carlo is the best
Best Italian restaurant in Baltimore.  Chef Carlo's an excellent host and truly gifted chef!

My husband and I stopped by here with a food tour group. We met the very personable chef and he told us about himself and his proud dishes. A couple of days later we had to come back, this time for dinner! The house made pasta is always amazing! For dessert we had the cheesecake and conolies. We both ordered drinks from the bar menu as well and they went nicely with our dinner. Compliments to our waitress Allison for the great service and her passion for the business! She was very fun and helpful as we asked about the different textures and flavors of the dishes.

One of the worst Italian meals I ever had. Went on the reviews here but was more than disappointed. Started with the Fritto Mixto which was bland and slightly greasy. The special salad with butter lettuce,arugula supposedly farm fresh was also bland. It was supposed to have pancetta but was served with some form of thinly sliced dry ham. The pears on it were thickly sliced but at least Sweet. My main meal was house linguini with seafood. The pasta was over cooked and the mussles were too shriveled and the few that weren’t had a super strong Oder and taste so I did not eat them. The other seafood on it was ok. The white wine olive oil and garlic sauce I requested in place of tomato sauce was thick and yellowish and tasted like flour. The waitress said they did not have time to reduce so they add potato starch. Sacrilegious! Also asked for extra garlic and had no taste of it. The chef/owner wasn’t there. If he was in the kitchen maybe it would have been different. I rarely complain but as a foodie and chef this was so disappointing. The staff was nice as an aside.
Excellent food and service. The manager was very helpful with the dinner selection. Will be back for the calamari.
Real Italian food
Loved the cocktail. Really loved my pasta dish.
Get the crab pasta.
If you are looking for an authentic Italian experience that's the place to go! The chef is amazing
Wonderful fresh pasta and great service. The chef came out to introduce himself and make sure we were pleased with his food. Just what you expect from a quality restaurant.

Fantastic place for anyone who loves great Italian food and deserts. Awesome service and atmosphere, friendly and professional servers with great attitudes. Owners are down to earth and take pride in their work.
Absolutely delicious food in a very nice building!
Damn fine meal!
Hidden gem
The food and service was simply amazing! You won’t regret your dining experience here! ❤️

Food is good but the service is slow. We had to flag down someone to find our server several times. I think they are short staffed. Unfortunately this is the same thing we experienced on previous visits.
The staff were excellent, the food was delicious everything was made from scratch the atmosphere is great
Great food, great service!! Lasagne was the best I have ever had!

Thought we’d been to every restaurant in little Italy but thank god we were wrong. Shout out to the GM Dave Olsen and our waiter Geri. Amazing food crazy accommodating staff and a wonderful dinner all around.  Wine could be cheaper but food keeps it five stars we’ll be back (and back). Thanks!
So good and the service was phenomenal.
excellent food and service with helpful recommendations. one of the best restaurants.
One of the best restaurants I've eaten at in a while. The waiter was very knowledgeable concerning the menu and made excellent suggestions. If I'm back in Baltimore anytime soon, I'll head here.
Good Food
Good food. Kinda expensive but it's a fancy date kind of place and I expected it.
Clean and cozy environment. Staffs were super friendly. Their calamari is the best.

Off the chain. Came up for an Orioles game from Miami and decided to search for good Italian food. This place came up with good ratings on both trip advisor and google / sure enough the capalini puttanesca was amazing my wife had something great and my kids had the spaghetti bolognese and Daniel our server was awesome

Amazing hidden gem! This is authentic italian. The food is made with pride and love ; every bite is amazing and makes you want to go back for more. This is the type of place that you can choose anything on the menu and you will not go wrong. Take a chance go eat here- you will not regret it. It will become one of your favorites.

This place was exceptional...a hidden gem in Baltimores Little Italy neighborhood just a few blocks away from the ultra touristy inner harbor. Our server, Keith, was knowledgeable and attentive, walking us through the menu like a captivating short story. The food is all fresh and from scratch and you could taste it. The homemade pasta is just plain perfect and the sauces have such delicate flavor you want to to eat every last drop. Seafood was all fresh and perfectly cooked to boot. Can't wait to return as we didn't have room for dessert this time around!

I cannot say enough good things about La Tavola.  Amazing food and incredible service.  Always a treat and a pleasure to dine there.  Their housemade limoncello is a must have when visiting Ls Tavola .
Great experience! Keith was awesome, as was all the food and wine! Will definitely be back!
Great food, great service!
Amazing staff with amazing homemade pasta!
Simply amazing in every aspect!! Will definitely be back!
Baltimore Bikeshare
